      • add

        public abstract void add​(Vector vector)
        Adds vector to this.

      • compact

        public void compact​(java.util.List<MutablePoints.Interval> intervals)
        Removes all the vectors from this which are not contained in any of the intervals. This is done by moving all the intervals to the start of this then setting the new size of this to to the sum of the length of all of the intervals.
        Parameters:
        intervals - disjunct intervals of this containing valid vectors

      • copy

        protected void copy​(int from,
                    int to,
                    int length)
        Copies the interval of vectors [from, from+length) to [to, to+length). The intervals must not overlap.

      • size

        public abstract void size​(int size)
        Sets the size of this to size. If the new size is smaller than the old size then vectors are deleted from this. If the new size is larger than the old size then vectors are created to this with undefined coordinate values.

      • subPoints

        public abstract MutablePoints subPoints​(int fromIndex,
                                        int toIndex)
        Creates a MutablePoints that has the same vectors as this in the interval [fromIndex, toIndex). The only mutator method sub-points have to support is swap().
